If you don&#39;t want to use swing timers then create a thread and post your UI code back to the UI thread like this:

    Runnable r = new Runnable() {
                    
        public void run() {
                        
             while (condition holds) {
                //sleep, do work, etc.

                //Post UI code back to the Swing thread
                SwingUtilities.invokeLater(() -&gt; { //some ui code }
             }
        }
    };
    
    Thread t = new Thread(r);
    t.start();

